  "prompt": "What is the meaning of sending nudge in hike messenger?",
  "response": "In Hike Messenger, sending a **\"nudge\"** is a way to gently remind or prompt someone to respond to your message. It's essentially a notification or alert that you send to the recipient, which can be in the form of a buzz, sound, or visual cue on their device. The purpose of a nudge is to draw their attention back to the conversation if they haven\u2019t replied yet.\n\nTo send a nudge in Hike Messenger, you typically long-press on the message you\u2019ve sent and select the \"Nudge\" option. This feature is designed to make communication more interactive and ensure that important messages don\u2019t get overlooked. It\u2019s a polite and non-intrusive way to check in without sending another text.",
